\question[40]

Councilman Burgess wishes to have a chart that shows the monthly firearms seizures in each neighborhood by year and compare this to the incidence of violent crimes in each neighborhood by month and year since 2015.  Assume that you already have the violent crimes data in whatever form you need.  

\begin{parts}
  \part Draw a flow chart of a process that prepares the firearms seizure data so that each line shows the total number of firearms seized in each neighborhood in Council District 9 in a month, sorted by neighborhood and date.
  \part Sketch out a plot that does this.  
  \part Explain how your plot fits the criteria provided (i.e. state the visual cue for each part of the specification)
\end{parts}

\begin{solution}
Flow chart should include a filter (council district), a group by (neighborhood, month, year), and summation (count).

Example plot.  One plot (facet) per year, stacked bar plot with firearms seizures x axis has months, each color (stacked) is a neighborhood. Add a line plot to show violent crimes (potentially with another axis)

Points off for missing an aspect (by neighborhood, by month, or violent crimes)
