A regional supermarket chain is deciding whether to install a tewgit machine in each of its stores.  Each machine costs \$250,000. Projected cash flows per machine is in Table \ref{tbl:tewgit}.

\begin{table}[]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{lrrrrrr}
\hline
Year & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & 5 \\
\hline
Cost  & -250 &  &  &  &  &  \\
Sales &  & 250 & 300 &  300 & 250 & 250 \\
Operating Expenses &  & -200 &  -200 &  -200 &  -200 &  -200 \\
\end{tabular}
\caption{Tewgit machine cash flow 1000s of dollars \label{tbl:tewgit}}
\end{table}

\begin{parts}
\part Draw the flow chart that presents how to calculate present value from future value given the future value, the number of time periods, and the interest rate.  This flow chart should be at the level of detail of each block showing one step of arithmetic (add, subtract, multiply, divide, exponent)
\part Draw the flow chart that demonstrates how to find the present value of the entire cash flow presented in the table.
\end{parts}

\begin{solution}

1. Multiple discount rate by number of periods

2. Multiply future value by result of 1

3. Apply PV to original cost

4. Apply PV to each value of sale

5. Apply PV to each value of ongoing costs
\end{solution}


